Morphology. General features —Idiosoma roundish; Cxgl– 4 subapical, only slightly posterior of Cx-I tips; posterior suture lines of Cx-IV extending back beyond posterior margin of genital field; excretory pore and Vgl– 2 clearly posterior to the line of primary sclerotization, excretory pore slightly posterior (
Fig. 1 B
), or on the level with Vgl– 2 (ventral view:
Fig. 2 A
,
14 A
) (
Fig. 2 A
); gnathosomal rostrum long, ventral margin in lateral view sharply curved (
Fig. 1 D
); P- 2 shorter than P- 4 , P- 2 with a long and slender, anteriorly directed ventrodistal projection; P- 3 ventrodistal protrusion shorter, cone shaped; P- 4 slender, with well developed ventral protuberances, ending in two tips separated by a concavity and bearing one very long and three short setae (
Figs. 1 C
,
2 B
). Male: genital field subrectangular in shape; ejaculatory complex normal in shape (proximal and distal arms and proximal chamber well developed,
Fig. 2 C
). Female: genital field pentagonal in shape, anteriorly enlarged and strongly tapering posteriorly.

